[Jefferson County, with a population of 116 229 residents in 2010, is on the northeastern border of the U.S. state of New York, adjacent to Lake Ontario and the St. Laurence River; its county seat is Watertown (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jefferson_County,_New_York). A map that shows the location of Jefferson County can be found at https://www.google.com/maps/place/Jefferson+County,+NY. - Mod.ML]

******
[2] Kentucky
Date: Wed 16 Oct 2019
Source: WPSD Local6 [edited]
https://www.wpsdlocal6.com/news/whooping-cough-cases-linked-to-decreased-vaccinations-in-adults/article_ca8f8570-f056-11e9-969b-0b4893e1cf6f.html


Whooping cough can be deadly for babies and tough on adults, too. In Kentucky, there have been 8 confirmed cases this year [2019].

Data from the U.S. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention show a rise in cases in Kentucky and a decrease in vaccinations. The latest CDC data show that from 2017 to 2018, the number of Tdap vaccinations decreased by 1.4%. The number of cases of whooping cough increased to more than 10 cases per 100 000 people.

Knight [a nurse at the Purchase District Health Department] said the lack of vaccines for adults and a false sense of security [are] contributing to this increase. "If your child was the one that couldn't have the immunization, you would want everyone else around them to have it," Knight said. "And to keep them in mind that you're doing it for your child, because you don't want them to get this disease."

[Byline: Abisola Adeyemo]

