[3] Nevada (Washoe County)
Date: Tue 22 Oct 2019
Source: U.S. News & World Report [edited]
https://www.usnews.com/news/best-states/nevada/articles/2019-10-22/whooping-cough-outbreak-closes-private-reno-high-school


A whooping cough outbreak has prompted the closure of a private high school in Reno [Nevada] until next week. The Washoe County Health District says it has confirmed 4 cases of whooping cough at Bishop Manogue High School. Additional cases are probable.

District officials say the Catholic school is cooperating with an investigation into the highly contagious respiratory disease and agreed to close the school until Monday [28 Oct 2019] to protect students and staff.

District Health officer Kevin Dick said late Monday [21 Oct 2019] that the outbreak is "very serious." He says it underscores why all students are required to be vaccinated for the disease, which is called "pertussis" and is known for uncontrollable, violent coughing that makes it hard to breathe.

Washoe County School District officials say no other cases have been confirmed at any other schools in the Reno-Sparks area.

